=== EXAMPLE: scdoc_Classes_EnvGate_ex1 ===

DESCRIPTION: A neutral pure_tone sound, with complex oscillator character around 80 Hz, featuring punchy attack and dynamic envelope, with chaotic spectral movement, filtered with resonant_steep_rolloff character, and spectrally rich.

CATEGORIES:
  attack_time: punchy
  brightness: neutral
  crest_factor_db: dynamic
  envelope_flatness: flat
  harmonic_to_noise_ratio: pure_tone
  spectral_complexity_mean: rich
  spectral_flux_normalized: chaotic
  spectral_slope: steep_rolloff
  temporal_centroid: balanced

SYNTHESIS CONCEPTS (key values):
[oscillator]
  fundamental_freq: 80.2923
  harmonic_decay_rate: -2.3379
  harmonic_regularity: 0.6615
  pitch_clarity: 81.4809
  inharmonicity: 0.0058
  type: complex
[filter]
  spectral_slope: -35.9891
  resonance_freq: 150.7324

SUPERCOLLIDER CODE:
// Title: EnvGate Example 1
// Author: SC Documentation
// URL: http://doc.sccode.org/Classes/EnvGate.html
// Tags: EnvGate, Classes, envelope
// ---
// --- Example 1 ---
a = { LPF.ar(Saw.ar(200), 600) * EnvGate.new }.play;
a.set(\fadeTime, 2);
a.release;

// the same as:
a.set(\gate, 0);

// several env gates can coexist in one synth def.
(
a = {
    var sound1 = LPF.ar(Saw.ar(80), 600) * EnvGate.new;
    var sound2 = RLPF.ar(Saw.ar(200) * 0.5, 6000 * EnvGate.new + 60, 0.1) * EnvGate.new;
    sound1 + sound2
}.play;
)
a.set(\fadeTime, 5);
a.release;
